I have two observations on the above:

1. Why aren't the __en and __out variables being declared?
2. I see that verilator examines the usage of the signals to determine if __en and __out are needed. Could I request that for the top-level module, they are added unconditionally? Or at least have a method of figuring out via `#ifdef` if the variables __en or __out are present (to avoid compile errors such as the above).
